ocked user cannot send you messages or chat with you in games.<\/li>\n  <li>They are unable to join your private servers or invite you to groups.<\/li>\n  <li>Your avatar will not be visible to them in games or friend lists.<\/li>\n  <li>Friends who are blocked will be removed from your friends list automatically.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nThis level of restriction is designed to provide effective protection while maintaining the platform’s social functionality.\n\n<h3>Limitations and Considerations<\/h3>\n\nWhile blocking is effective, it has some limitations:\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Blocked users can still see your public games and play alongside you if the game is public and you share the same server.<\/li>\n  <li>Blocking does not prevent users from creating new accounts to circumvent restrictions, a common issue known as “ban evasion.”<\/li>\n  <li>For severe cases of harassment, blocking should be combined with reporting to Roblox’s moderation team.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nUnderstanding these nuances helps users implement comprehensive safety strategies rather than relying solely on blocking.\n\n<h2>Enhancing Safety: Additional Roblox Privacy Settings<\/h2>\n\nBeyond blocking, Roblox offers several privacy controls to customize who can contact you or interact in your games:\n\n<h3>Chat and Messaging Controls<\/h3>\n\nUsers can restrict chat permissions through the Privacy settings, choosing options such as:\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Allowing chat only with friends.<\/li>\n  <li>Disabling private messages altogether.<\/li>\n  <li>Filtering out inappropriate content using Roblox’s chat filter system.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h3>Friend Request Management<\/h3>\n\nLimiting friend requests to “No one” or “Friends of Friends” reduces the risk of unwanted contacts, thereby minimizing the need to block users later.\n\n<h3>Account Restrictions for Younger Users<\/h3>\n\nRoblox provides additional safety features for accounts under 13 years old, including stricter chat filters and limited communication options. 